==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castoreum
<hw>Cas*to"re*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Castor</er>.]</ety> <def>A peculiar bitter orange-brown substance,
with strong, penetrating odor, found in two sacs between the anus and
external genitals of the beaver; castor; -- used in medicine as an
antispasmodic, and by perfumers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castoridae</ent>⟦br⟧
